
Headline: Another lab down! Just wrapped up BTLO's "The Report" investigation.

This challenge drops you into a newly established SOC tasked with turning a massive 2022 Threat Detection Report into actionable security rules.

Quick hits on what I focused on:

MITRE T1059 (Command & Scripting): Seen in over 50% of environments. 
It highlights why understanding baseline administrative behavior is crucial for catching Living off the Land tactics.

Malicious Scripting: Why detection engineering rules need to flag wscript.exe executing untrusted scripts rather than just watching standard command prompts.

The Affiliate Model: Tracking how initial access brokers use precursors like Qbot and BazarLoader to pave the way for ransomware groups like Conti.

Continuous skill-sharpening is everything in defense. On to the next challenge! 

